Data type in java
- mainly we have 2 types of datatype
1) primitive data type
2) non-primitive data type

1) primitive data type
- data size is fixed
- we have 3 types of primitive data type
a) numeric data type
- According to data size we divide numeric data type
- byte
- small
- int
-long
-float
- double

b) char
- byte ( all char )

c)boolean
- bit ( true 0r false )

2) Non-primitive data type
- data size is not fixed
- we have 3 types of Non-primitive data type
a) Class
b) Array
c) string

